.TH "reserve_space" 9 "reserve_space" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
reserve_space \- reserve space in the journal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" reserve_space
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "int jhead "  ","
.BI "int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "jhead" 12
journal head number
.IP "len" 12
node length
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function reserves space in journal head \fIhead\fP. If the reservation
succeeded, the journal head stays locked and later has to be unlocked using
'\fBrelease_head\fP'. Returns zero in case of success, -EAGAIN if commit has to
be done, and other negative error codes in case of other failures.
